#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:17
msgid ""
"To add a label, click the |label| :sup:`Add label` icon, place the "
"element with the left mouse button on the Print Composer canvas and "
"position and customize its appearance in the label :guilabel:`Item "
"Properties` panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:21
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Item Properties` panel of a label item provides the "
"following functionality for the label item (see Figure_composer_label_):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:29
msgid "Label Item Properties Panel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:32
msgid "Main properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:34
msgid ""
"The main properties dialog is where the text (HTML or not) or the "
"expression needed to fill the label is added to the Composer canvas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:36
msgid ""
"Labels can be interpreted as HTML code: check |checkbox| "
":guilabel:`Render as HTML`. You can now insert a URL, a clickable image "
"that links to a web page or something more complex."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:39
msgid ""
"You can also insert an expression. Click on **[Insert an expression]** to"
" open a new dialog. Build an expression by clicking the functions "
"available in the left side of the panel. Two special categories can be "
"useful, particularly associated with the atlas functionality: "
"**geometry** and **records** functions. At the bottom, a preview of the "
"expression is shown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:46
msgid "Appearance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:48
msgid ""
"Define :guilabel:`Font` by clicking on the **[Font...]** button or a "
":guilabel:`Font color` selecting a color using the color selection tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:50
msgid ""
"You can specify different horizontal and vertical margins in ``mm``. This"
" is the margin from the edge of the composer item. The label can be "
"positioned outside the bounds of the label e.g. to align label items with"
" other items. In this case you have to use negative values for the "
"margin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_label.rst:54
msgid ""
"Using the :guilabel:`Alignment` is another way to position your label. "
"Note that when e.g. using the :guilabel:`Horizontal alignment` in "
"|radioButtonOn| :guilabel:`Center` Position the :guilabel:`Horizontal "
"margin` feature is disabled."
msgstr ""

